He said, “I will hide my face from them.
I will see what their end will be;
for they are a very perverse generation,
children in whom is no faithfulness.

if I sharpen my glittering sword,
my hand grasps it in judgment;
I will take vengeance on my adversaries,
and will repay those who hate me.

He said of his father, and of his mother, ‘I have not seen him.’
He didn’t acknowledge his brothers,
nor did he know his own children;
for they have observed your word,
and keep your covenant.

About Joseph he said,
“His land is blessed by Yahweh,
for the precious things of the heavens, for the dew,
for the deep that couches beneath,

About Zebulun he said,
“Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going out;
and Issachar, in your tents.

Blessed is the man who doesn’t walk in the counsel of the wicked,
nor stand on the path of sinners,
nor sit in the seat of scoffers;

Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end,
but establish the righteous;
their minds and hearts are searched by the righteous God.

Have mercy on me, Yahweh.
See my affliction by those who hate me,
and lift me up from the gates of death;

For I have heard the slander of many, terror on every side,
while they conspire together against me,
they plot to take away my life.

All my bones shall say, “Yahweh, who is like you,
who delivers the poor from him who is too strong for him;
yes, the poor and the needy from him who robs him?”

God has spoken once;
twice I have heard this,
that power belongs to God.

while you sleep among the camp fires,
the wings of a dove sheathed with silver,
her feathers with shining gold.

Reproach has broken my heart, and I am full of heaviness.
I looked for some to take pity, but there was none;
for comforters, but I found none.

Your righteousness also, God, reaches to the heavens;
you have done great things.
God, who is like you?

My tongue will also talk about your righteousness all day long,
for they are disappointed, and they are confounded,
who want to harm me.

Remember your congregation, which you purchased of old,
which you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance;
Mount Zion, in which you have lived.
